President Joe Biden has declared a major disaster in Montana due to severe storm and flooding that occurred starting on June 10, 2022. This declaration allows for federal assistance to supplement state, tribal, and local recovery efforts in the affected areas. The counties of Carbon, Park, and Stillwater are eligible for federal funding on a cost-sharing basis for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures statewide. Maona N. Ngwira has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected areas, and additional designations may be made if requested by the state and warranted by further damage assessments. For more information, media can contact the FEMA News Desk.